        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 2:59PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 259 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Milliken, or 12 miles southwest of Greeley, moving southeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Southeastern Greeley, Evans, Johnstown, Milliken, Berthoud, Mead,
Platteville, LaSalle, Gilcrest, Garden City, Fort St Vrain,
Peckham and Lower Latham Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
